Text.Value: Your purpose is clear as welts on an infant's skin: you come for our Netherstones next.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player didn't tell Orin they want her netherstone - she thinks they lied, and is amused by it. Proof of how pathetic they are.

Text.Value: I'm here looking for my next angle, but it's all the same - oppression, famine, death. I need something new. Someone like you.
I've no interest in the Absolute. I'm here strictly on personal matters.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [LOGAN] Lens drops the notebook as she jerks about, transforming back into Orin.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The journalist's body jerks as she transforms, wildshape-style into Orin the Red.

Text.Value: Let me stop you there. We'll need to be a bit more focused. Word counts, you know.

EditorData.NodeContext: Polite redirect

Text.Value: You think chaos courses through your veins? You have no idea...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a malicious smile. [LOGAN] Orin / Lens begins to drop the act. She winds down her writing.
EditorData.NodeContext: ominous

Text.Value: I seek a path to freedom. The less said, the better.
Consider me an emissary of my people.
Be as water. Move as a river - strike like a tsunami. I will drown this fetid cult.
You must have some strategy in mind?
I'm going to cut that rotten cult off at the head - take out its leaders.
Have you come beg-begging, sniffing for our stones? Gortash won't like that. A throat his black hand can't choke the spit from.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking, finds your plan ridiculous but enjoys the chaos it will cause. 'Stones' are the netherstones. 'Black hand' reference to the 'Black Hand of Bane', Gortash's god.

Text.Value: It won't take more than two moments of your time. If you play your cards right, this could make the cover. I just need some extra details.
I ground his bones to dust. Even his god could not save him.
You must have been dreaming of this day for some time. No doubt the thought kept you going despite the perils you faced to get here.
You shed your secrets so easily. No matter - your clumsy purpose is clear enough already.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking - thinks you're pathetic.

Text.Value: Though, if anyone could help him, it would be you. You've a knack for finding chinks in the Absolute's armour.
How wonderful. No doubt your reunion will be filled with tales from your recent adventures in the shadow-cursed lands.
I fought with everything I had. He was a formidable foe wielding terrible power.
You come for mine too, slaughter-kin. And I hunger for yours.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player previously revealed their plan to Orin. She knows they want her netherstone. Likes the idea they want to challenge her

Text.Value: You'll deal with the remaining Absolutists in much the same way, I suppose.
So you're the lickspittle who crushed the Bone Lord's thrall.

EditorData.NodeContext: First time Orin meets player. 'Bone Lord's thrall' is Ketheric, who player previously killed. Curious.

Text.Value: Hold on. What do you want with me?
None of your business.
My sources tell me you recently vanquished the fearsome General Ketheric Thorm. How did you manage that?
Defying the gods themselves? I had no idea.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: And any family would be proud to have such a son representing them. Especially after your exploits in the shadow-cursed lands.
Let's just say Myrkul's apostle was no match of a dusting of faerie magic.
I can be diabolically clever - Myrkul's Chosen wasn't ready.
I drowned him in a darkness older and more profound than any he claimed to command.
An interview about what?
My intentions aren't fit for printing. Trust me.
Liar.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a malicious smile. [LOGAN] Orin / Lens begins to drop the act. She winds down her writing.
EditorData.NodeContext: ominous

Text.Value: Aren't you - I knew there was a story here, and there you are, the hero of the hour, walking right up to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Delighted

Text.Value: I'm sure you were much more than that. You proved to be quite the thorn in his side.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: You have? But I thought our soon-to-be Lord Gortash had things in hand?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Formidable? You're just being modest. I heard you swatted him aside like a fly from a corpse.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Everybody needs a rest from time to time, even seasoned adventurers like yourself.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Like many before him and many after, Ketheric fell to his own hubris. I was merely present.
Ketheric's hubris was his downfall. I was merely the catalyst.
I've had enough. This interview's over.
Oh you know, taking a holiday, visiting family. Normal reasons.
Unfortunately the version I heard was light on details. So what did you do to Ketheric?
Don't worry. I already have everything I need.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a malicious smile [LOGAN] Orin / Lens begins to drop the act. She winds down her writing.
EditorData.NodeContext: Ominous

Text.Value: The cult's threat is far from extinguished. What's your plan of attack?
So you were forced to kill him? What a tragic story.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [DG] Laezel (Orin) transforms into her true form.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: SHORT Orin transforms.

Text.Value: You think you can hide your purpose. You are a brutish butcher, your blunted skull has no vision for deceit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player didn't tell Orin they want her netherstone - she thinks they lied. Giving you a dressing down - all the ways you're inferior to her. 'Blunted skull' alluding to the tadpole in your brain.

Text.Value: Remember - his throat spits lies, but my blade carves the truth. You will read it on your skin soon enough.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orin twists her ring and disappears.
EditorData.NodeContext: toying with the player, knows the 'truth' about them and is enjoying holding this against them

Text.Value: Taking out one of the Absolute's generals was no mean feat. You must feel confident for the battles ahead.
You think I can't sniff the secrets hidden in your pretty skull? What you seek. What you need.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking - thinks you're pathetic.

Text.Value: I'm a journalist. It's my job to know everything.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: You're planning to indulge yourself in some of the darker corners of the city. No need to hide anything - we're all sinners by someone's yardstick.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Not much of a planner, I'm afraid. More of an improviser.
Sounds like you're planning to make quite the impression. Only to be expected, given your feats in the shadow-cursed lands.
Look at it, come crawling home, hands stained with the Bone Lord's soot. And you carry his stone.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'It' is the Dark Urge player. 'Home' at this point is just the city, not yet the temple. 'Bone Lord's soot' refers to the player having killed Ketheric (his god Myrkul is the Lord of Bones)

Text.Value: Returning to the fold with plenty of tales to tell, I'm sure. Not least about your adventures in the shadow-cursed lands.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Do not worry, slaughter kin. My blades are still sharp and sweet. They will greet you soon enough.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orin twists her ring and disappears.
EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking reassurance - trying to make the player uneasy.

Text.Value: How about I ask a few questions, and you just tell me the first thing that comes into your head?
Unfortunately, Absolutists rarely seem interested in compromise.
How in the Hells do you know about that?
Quickly, then. I've urgent business in the city.
My life's in danger. I've come to find a way to save myself.
A portentous arrival then. Your inheritance awaits - one you feel you've earned ten times over, I don't doubt.
The name's Lens, reporter with the Baldur's Mouth Gazette. Care to do a quick interview?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [LOGAN] Pulls out pen and notebook much like *REUSE* CINE_Observe_TakeNotes_01. Create Idle out of end pose:, Lens poised ready to write.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Taking out a notebook and quill
EditorData.NodeContext: Pacy, excited - wants to get things moving quickly

Text.Value: Let's just say I'm here to leave my mark on the city. All will know of Gale of Waterdeep, soon enough.
So, you've arrived in Baldur's Gate. What's brought you here at a time like this?
Though from what I hear, you've little to fear from the Absolute.

EditorData.NodeContext: mentioning "Th Absolute" here should sound like a pivot - she's assuming this is the threat referred to

Text.Value: My birthright awaits me.
I imagine you've a need to let off some steam after your recent adventures in the shadow-cursed lands.
What makes you think I'm planning on attacking them?
I offered him a chance at redemption. When he refused to take it, he left me no choice.
Absolutely not.
Then consider this a taste of what's to come. You must be able to share something about Ketheric's downfall?
I could end it now - but I'll be patient. Father will see us together again. He will see you bleed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orin twists her ring and disappears.
EditorData.NodeContext: Toying with the player, trying to make them uneasy, establish her power over them. 'Father' is Bhaal.

Text.Value: Where to begin... Well, I was born the year of a poor harvest...
I need to return to some... colleagues, let's call them. They're expecting me.
I hardly want my strategy printed all over the front pages, do I?
I know the truth: you come for our Netherstones. Come to prise one from the tyrant's death grip, pluck the other from my rotted carcass.
Still rolling in the muck, I see.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking, thinks you're pathetic

Text.Value: His Absolutist friends can't be very happy with you.
Look, I'm going to write this piece with or without your input. It'll be much more accurate if you answer my questions.
Gortash knows you are coming. Knows you have the Bone Lord's stone. Do not let him hiss hot air into your worm-weakened brain.

EditorData.NodeContext: Acting like she's helping you, but just trying to freak you out. 'Bone Lord's stone' is Ketheric's netherstone

Text.Value: A noble purpose indeed. Baldur's Gate has many liberties to offer, especially for one with your skills.
And a noble and powerful people they must be, to be represented by one of your impressive experience.
You, of course. News travels fast in this city, and after your exploits, you're quite the celebrity. This interview will be our biggest issue yet.
I've come to save the city.
Perhaps it could inspire some like-minded citizens to help your cause.
I don't imagine they'll give you much choice, after you killed their general. Better to be on the front foot, surely?
You don't trust journalists? I'm not like the others - your words are safe with me.
You must have some plans once you enter the city?
Gortash, maybe. You'll find me much harder to kill...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a malicious smile. [LOGAN] Orin / Lens begins to drop the act. She winds down her writing.
EditorData.NodeContext: ominous

Text.Value: You think you're fit to wield the stones? A slipshod butcher, dull-skulled, unable to think, to create, to worship.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player previously revealed their plan to Orin. Giving you a dressing down - all the ways you're inferior to her

Text.Value: When you find the lordling, tell him Orin is watching.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Orin twists her ring and disappears.
EditorData.NodeContext: Playful, menacing. Trying to make player uneasy - she could be hiding anywhere.

Text.Value: I live here. Or did, anyway. This homecoming has been a long time coming.
I have... family business to attend to.
You came seeking safety in a city under siege? The threat must be dire indeed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Lens makes some notes. [LOGAN] Check with Greg, V.O performance similar to established pose of Lens writing.

Text.Value: Sorry, I'm saving that story for my memoirs.
I see how you slip-slither closer, belly dragging in the filth. Father is laughing at you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Second time Orin appeared to toy with you. She can't believe you're wasting so much time.

Text.Value: And I wouldn't dream of keeping you from it.
I... have to see an old acquaintance.

Synopsis:
At the end of the queue leading to the South span’s checkpoint is a young journalist taking note and quotes from the poor souls trying to get into Baldur’s Gate.

Lens, a female tiefling in a worn overcoat, can simply be a quiet news worker taking the beat of the outside city (because someone has to tell the true story).
